themes: business structure reform for creative industries
key_phrases: More support for full time musicians/artists/etc.
Highly skilled creative workers who contribute to multiple creative projects as their full time living.
Promotion of equity and higher standards for compensation for creative work throughout the city.
Incentivizing change to business structures to better compensate for creative work.
Modifying grant structures: less money per person, but spread across a wider net to reach more creatives more often.
More balanced coverage in the Austin Chronicle.
barriers_identified: insufficient support for full-time creative workers
business structures that do not adequately compensate creative work
grant structures that do not reach enough creatives
solutions_proposed: increase support for full-time musicians and artists
promote equity and higher compensation standards
incentivize business structure changes to better compensate creative work
modify grant structures to distribute less money per person but reach more creatives
ensure more balanced coverage in the Austin Chronicle
